Rating: 4
Very quick and easy. The spicy/sourness of the watercress works excellently with the cream sauce. The local market was all out of sea bass so I substituted fresh salmon. I also doubled the amount of sauce so 1/2 cup white wine - I used Orvieto - and 1/2 cup cream with 1/2 cup milk. I used a "bunch" of watercress so I'm not sure the exact measure but it was excellent. I served the fish over a bed of linguini and topped with the extra sauce.

Rating: 4
